nd dipping interval. The repeating absorption dips in MAXI J1803-298 are likely of the same nature as the nearly-periodic absorption dips seen in the light curves of some other X-ray binaries that are viewed at high inclination angles (>60 degrees). These recur on periods that are in general very close to the orbital periods of those systems. Given the limited NICER coverage of the dipping intervals in MAXI J1803-298 we suggest that the orbital period of the system is likely between 7 and 8 hrs, although an integer fraction of that cannot be ruled out with our data.},
